## 5. Vitest tests

**File:** `src/renderer/src/shared/utils/themeIO.test.ts` (NEW FILE)

Follow the style of `src/renderer/src/shared/hooks/useThemeApplicator.test.ts` — `import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest'`, inline fixtures, `describe` + `it` blocks.

Required coverage:

- `slugifyThemeName`: "Twilight" → `twilight`; "Warm Earth Dark" → `warm-earth-dark`; input of only punctuation/spaces → `theme`; runs of spaces collapse to one hyphen; leading/trailing hyphens trimmed
- `stripModeSuffix`: "Twilight Dark" → "Twilight"; "Twilight Light" → "Twilight"; "Pure" → "Pure" (no change); case-insensitive suffix match
- `serializeThemePair` + `validateThemeJson` round-trip: serialize a pair, re-validate and confirm the returned `theme.configs` equal the originals
- `validateThemeJson` failure modes — one test per kind:
  - `parse`: input `"not json"`
  - `marker`: valid JSON but missing `$todoozy` or with wrong value
  - `version`: `version: 2`
  - `name`: empty or whitespace-only `name`
  - `modes`: missing `configs.dark` or `configs.light`
  - `colors`: one color value is `"#xyz"` or missing
- `resolveImportName`: no collision → same name; single collision → `X (Imported)`; two collisions → `X (Imported 2)`; walks up to `(Imported 4)` when the first three suffixes all exist
- `errorToMessage`: asserts each kind returns a non-empty string (exhaustiveness)

## 6. Out-of-scope

Supabase `user_themes` table stores only 5 of 8 theme tokens (tracked as ToDoozy task `609ea5c2-02c3-407a-9c86-3719992a692b`). This story does NOT fix that gap. Do not modify `PersonalSyncService.ts`, `user_themes` table schema, or any Supabase migration in this story. Imported themes sync with the same partial fidelity as any other custom theme — that's acceptable for this story.

## 7. Edge cases checklist (what NOT to do)

- Do NOT auto-apply the imported theme as a separate special flow — call `setCurrentTheme(id)` the same way a dropdown change does
- Do NOT partially insert on validation failure — the error modal shows and no DB rows are created
- Do NOT show a toast on error — errors use the modal
- Do NOT add keyboard shortcuts
- Do NOT add a second-confirmation dialog after import (selection = application in ToDoozy)
- Do NOT touch `PersonalSyncService.ts` — the existing sync path handles imported themes
- Do NOT add backwards-compatibility code for single-mode files — imports require both `configs.dark` and `configs.light`
- Do NOT block import when the user is offline — saves locally; syncs on reconnect (existing behavior)

